text: Philippe Boënnec (born April 21, 1951 in Nantes) is a member of the National Assembly of France and represents the Loire-Atlantique department. He is a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1951 births Category:Living people Category:People from Nantes Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:The Social Right Category:Modern and Humanist France Category:The Popular Right Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
